        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35398",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can extract the authentication token from the Zend_Gdata_Apps object, and then store that.\r\n\r\nI'd prefer to avoid singletons whenever possible. What if a user wants to interact with two accounts simultaneously?\r\n\r\nI'm going to close this as Won't Fix.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-19T00:50:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-19T00:50:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35399",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=warden",
                        "name": "warden",
                        "displayName": "Radek Antoniuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm okay with that, then the class could provide a clear method for extracting the authentication token or a serializing method to save in the session. What do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=warden",
                        "name": "warden",
                        "displayName": "Radek Antoniuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-19T05:29:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-19T05:29:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35447",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is already implemented.\r\n\r\nSee Zend_Gdata_HttpClient::getClientLoginToken() and getAuthSubToken():\r\n\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/apidoc\/core\/Zend_Gdata\/Gdata\/Zend_Gdata_HttpClient.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-21T15:03:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-21T15:03:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35451",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=warden",
                        "name": "warden",
                        "displayName": "Radek Antoniuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for that.\r\nI'm just wondering now... it would be quite ok just to store the whole Zend_Gdata_Gapps object in session after authentication, provided that the password would not be stored in Zend_Gdata_Gapps::$_httpClient::$paramsPost and lastRequest.\r\nSo, maybe after successful authentication, it should do:\r\nZend_Gdata_Gapps::getHttpClient()->resetParameters() \r\nand\r\nZend_Gdata_Gapps::getHttpClient()->setLastRequest(\"\"); \/\/ this method does not exist\r\n\r\nwhat do you think?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=warden",
                        "name": "warden",
                        "displayName": "Radek Antoniuk",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-21T16:19:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-21T16:19:57.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
